generous /ˈdʒɛnərəs/

1. ADJ A generous person gives more of something, especially money, than is usual or expected. 慷慨的 

例： Dietler is generous with his time and money. 迪特勒在他的时间和金钱方面慷慨大方。 

2. generously ADV 慷慨地 [ADV with v] 

例： We would like to thank all the judges who gave so generously of their time. 我们想感谢所有慷慨地付出时间的裁判们。 

3. ADJ A generous person is friendly, helpful, and willing to see the good qualities in someone or something. 宽厚的 

例： He was always generous in sharing his enormous knowledge. 他一直不吝分享自己丰富的知识。 

4. generously ADV 宽厚地 [ADV with v] 

例： The students generously gave them instruction in social responsibility. 学生们欣然为他们讲解了社会责任。 

5. ADJ A generous amount of something is much larger than is usual or necessary. 大量的 

例： He should be able to keep his room tidy with the generous amount of storage space. 有大量的储物空间，他应该可以保持他房间的整洁。 

6. generously ADV 大量地 

例： Season the steaks generously with salt and pepper. 大量地使用盐和胡椒给牛排调味。

